<subSubSection id="4BDBE20F687561EE675F1044E306DA22" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="90D6BF864109F050296367EE10F98256" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="912B5C695B90C032798F8064CF8F09E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="5DF3C006B7CFAA532FF906A6F2D196CB" genus="I." lsidName="I. brachystachya" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="brachystachya">
<emphasis id="E24F2E31870642AA5832544C83788F50" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">I. brachystachya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in its digitately compound, 5-7 foliolate leaves (versus pinnately compound, 7-9 foliolate leaves), leaflets 4-6 mm long (versus leaflets 9-15 mm long), racemes up to 7 mm long, flowers 
<normalizedToken id="D89F1F2F1E59C51BDA80A2F6BCD0E1C8" originalValue="Â±">+/-</normalizedToken>
4-5 per raceme (versus racemes&gt; 10 mm long, flowers&gt; 8 per raceme), flowers creamy white, unscented (versus flowers pale pink, scented), branching divaricate (versus branching random), populations restricted to sandstone fynbos (versus populations restricted to limestone fynbos).
</paragraph>
